Pre-Game Insights: England manager Gareth Southgate may not risk captain Harry Kane due to a back injury, with Aston Villa talisman Ollie Watkins likely to lead the line.
Manchester United duo Luke Shaw and Harry Maguire, along with Anthony Gordon, are on the recovery trail.
Bukayo Saka is rested ahead of Friday's match against Iceland, so Cole Palmer and Eberechi Eze are likely to start.
Declan Rice and Conor Gallagher are ahead in the pecking order, while Trent Alexander-Arnold could be tested in a midfield slot.
Marc Guehi and Lewis Dunk are expected to benefit in the backline, with Jordan Pickford, Ezri Konsa, and Kieran Trippier also in the lineup.
